text: Qarwa Uqhu (Quechua qarwa pale, yellowish, golden, uqhu swamp, "yellowish swamp", hispanicized spelling Carhua Ojo) is a mountain in the Andes of Peru, about high. It is located in the Ayacucho Region, Lucanas Province, Chipao District, southeast of Waytayuq. == References == Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Ayacucho Region
title: Qarwa Uqhu
